eople will go to in pursuit of safety, security and the futures they aspire to. Interdisciplinary in nature, the book champions a new political economy analysis of wellbeing in the context of migration and demonstrates the urgent need for policy reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChild welfare. 0aImmigration enforcement. 0aUnaccompanied immigrant childrenxSocial conditions. 0aWell-being. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aAllsopp, Jennifer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBhabha, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311119671840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529209051423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529209051/original  a978-3-11-119671-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles